Preserved moss is a medium that can underscore the significance of even the simplest message or image. Luxury property owners and designers all over the world love combining the color and texture of moss with their brand. These designers know that humans have been living in close proximity with plants for all of history. Adding these quiet, living creatures to your space simply makes it feel like home. You will find that in many design cases, the proper plant art can supplement and enhance a building’s core mission and vision. You could bring the beauty of nature to your property through work similar to installations Plant the Future has done at luxury locations including:

<strong><a href="https://plantthefuture.com/project/1-hotel-south-beach/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><img class="alignleft wp-image-1874" src="https://plantthefuture.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/Screen-Shot-2018-05-11-at-4.28.25-PM-300x246.png" alt="Custom Moss Wall Designs for Luxury Properties" width="205" height="168" /></a>1. 1 Hotel Miami Beach</strong>
<p style="text-align: left;">The <a href="https://plantthefuture.com/project/1-hotel-south-beach/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">1 Hotel in Miami Beach</a> is known worldwide as a luxury eco-destination. Plant the Future’s work here includes an Iconic Moss Mural done in collaboration with 2Alas, a large scale interior garden behind the reception desk, preserved mushrooms all around the lobby area, hanging orchids dripping with vines terrariums and tabletop succulent arrangements, and more. This space luxuriates in the tropical attractions of South Florida, bringing all the colors and shapes of the natural environment there.</p>
