<h3><a href="https://plantthefuture.com/project/1-hotel-south-beach/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><img class="alignleft wp-image-1914 " src="https://plantthefuture.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/Contemporary-Landscape-Design-Concepts-for-High-End-Resorts-292x300.jpg" alt="Contemporary Landscape Design Concepts for High End Resorts" width="225" height="231" /></a>1 Hotel in Miami, Florida: Nature Meets Luxury in this Contemporary Style</h3>
<strong> </strong>

The <a href="https://plantthefuture.com/project/1-hotel-south-beach/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">1 Hotel in Miami</a> has a landscape rich with contemporary moss art displays, terrariums, floor plants, wall applications made out of dried mushrooms, hanging orchids, indoor gardens, and botanical displays. Guests can enjoy the lush, green hallways, the intricate details of the cacti planters in the room, and the comical animal figurines used to add a light touch to the elegant marbled architecture.

<hr />

&nbsp;
<h3><a href="https://plantthefuture.com/project/palmademallorca/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><img class="alignleft wp-image-1915 " src="https://plantthefuture.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/Contemporary-Landscape-Design-Concepts-for-High-End-Resorts_1-298x300.jpg" alt="Contemporary Landscape Design Concepts for High End Resorts" width="230" height="232" /></a>Mushroom Reef: Resort-style Luxury at a Private Residence</h3>
<strong> </strong>

Completed last year, this <a href="https://plantthefuture.com/project/palmademallorca/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">beautiful mushroom display</a> calls to mind the intricacies and delicacy of coral caverns under the sea. The mushrooms are placed in organic, ascending patterns. There is variance in the coloration, with some mushrooms a bright white, others a gleaming silver, and others a natural, woodsy brown. The Mushrooms are associated with healing, magic and meditation, all perfect elements to bring to a living space.

<hr />

&nbsp;
<h3><a href="https://plantthefuture.com/project/starbuckscollins/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><img class="alignleft wp-image-1916 " src="https://plantthefuture.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/Contemporary-Landscape-Design-Concepts-for-High-End-Resorts_2-300x272.jpg" alt="Contemporary Landscape Design Concepts for High End Resorts" width="237" height="214" /></a>Draw Inspiration for High-End Resorts from the Biophilic Design in Starbucks, Miami</h3>
<strong> </strong>

Starbucks prides itself on fostering positive relationships with the farmers who grow their coffee beans. They emphasized their commitment to responsible sourcing through the use of art and design at the company’s <a href="https://plantthefuture.com/project/starbuckscollins/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Miami location</a> in Miami Beach. The artwork includes 3D sculptures, wall art worked in moss, and tabletop pieces. One of the wall pieces is a 2D map of the world, emphasizing the global, international characteristic of the brand.

