<h3><a href="https://plantthefuture.com/project/el-clasico/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><img class="alignleft wp-image-1917 " src="https://plantthefuture.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/Contemporary-Landscape-Design-Concepts-for-High-End-Resorts_3-300x251.jpg" alt="Contemporary Landscape Design Concepts for High End Resorts" width="230" height="192" /></a>Portraits of El Classico: An Example of the Custom Design Used in High-End Resorts</h3>
<strong> </strong>

These <a href="https://plantthefuture.com/project/el-clasico/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Portraits of El Classico</a> are a tribute to the Real Madrid players of the Real Madrid vs. FC Barcelona’s historic match in Miami on July 29, 2017. Artists Paloma Teppa and Andrew Antonaccio created the first exhibition of its kind with moss portraits of the players. The concept is to explore the playful result of merging Teppa’s whimsical work with plants with the optical work of Antonaccio.

